INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (385, 'Victorian Liberal Leader Distances Party from Federal Nuclear Proposal', 'Brad Battin says \'no thanks\' to Dutton\'s nuclear dreams, preferring gas over glowing reactors.', 'In a move that\'s less \"team player\" and more \"I\'m not with him,\" Victorian Liberal leader Brad Battin has artfully sidestepped federal counterpart Peter Dutton\'s grand nuclear ambitions. While Dutton dreams of dotting the Australian landscape with shiny new nuclear reactors, including one at Victoria\'s own Loy Yang power station, Battin is humming a different tuneone that sounds suspiciously like \"Gas, Gas, Baby.\" \r\nThe Guardian\r\n+5\r\nThe Guardian\r\n+5\r\nnews\r\n+5\r\nABC\r\n+3\r\nYahoo News Australia\r\n+3\r\nThe Guardian\r\n+3\r\n\r\nBattin, who ascended to the Victorian Liberal throne in December 2024 after a Game of Thrones-esque party shuffle, has been busy crafting his \"just a regular bloke\" image. From pub chats to policy talks, he\'s all about connecting with the everyday voter. But when it comes to Dutton\'s nuclear proposal, Battin\'s stance is clear: \"Our focus is gas.\" Translation? \"Nuclear? Not in my backyard, mate.\" \r\nThe Guardian\r\n\r\nThe backdrop to this political tango is Dutton\'s bold plan to erect seven nuclear reactors nationwide, with the Loy Yang site in Victoria\'s Latrobe Valley earmarked as a prime spot. However, this vision clashes head-on with Victoria\'s longstanding ban on nuclear activities, enshrined in the Nuclear Activities (Prohibitions) Act of 1983. Overturning this would be akin to convincing a vegan to run a butcher shop. \r\nABC\r\n+7\r\nSBS Australia\r\n+7\r\nYahoo News Australia\r\n+7\r\nThe Guardian\r\n\r\nBattin\'s gas-centric focus isn\'t just a random choice. With local gas fields on the decline and energy prices doing their best impression of a rollercoaster, he sees onshore gas exploration as the quick fix to keep Victorians\' lights on and wallets intact. Meanwhile, Dutton\'s nuclear daydreams are viewed by some as the political equivalent of building castles in the airgrand, but lacking a solid foundation. \r\ninkl\r\n+6\r\nThe Guardian\r\n+6\r\nThe Guardian\r\n+6\r\n\r\nAs of now, the Victorian Liberals are sticking to their gas guns, leaving Dutton to champion his nuclear crusade solo. Battin\'s message to Dutton? \"Good luck with that, but we\'re good over here with our gas plans.\" It\'s a classic case of political \"agree to disagree,\" with a side of \"please don\'t drag us into this.\" \r\nRenewEconomy\r\ninkl\r\n+6\r\nThe Guardian\r\n+6\r\nnews\r\n+6', 0, 'factabot', 'Victorian_Liberal_Leader_Distances_Party_from_Federal_Nuclear_Proposal', 'draft', NULL, NULL, '2025-04-15 07:22:11', '2025-04-15 07:22:11', 0);
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (386, 'Rory McIlroy Completes Career Grand Slam at The Masters', 'McIlroy finally dons the green jacket, proving that patience (and a killer swing) pays off.', 'It finally happened. Rory Almost There McIlroy has actually won The Masters, completing the career Grand Slam after 17 years of Augusta foreplay. Yes, the man whos been ghosting the green jacket since 2007 finally sealed the deal in 2025, joining the ultra-exclusive club of Golf Guys Whove Won Everythingalongside legends like Tiger Woods and Jack Nicklaus, and presumably a few golf-course ghosts. +Wikipedia\r\n\r\nMcIlroys win wasnt exactly textbook. The man racked up four double bogeyssetting a Masters record for most disasters survived en route to victory. But like any good protagonist in a sports movie, he ignored the bad script and pulled off a sudden-death playoff win over Justin Rose, who now knows what it feels like to be the bridesmaid, again. Rory, meanwhile, cried, hugged his wife Erica, and daughter Poppy like hed just broken a decade-long curse which, to be fair, he had. His last major win was in 2014, when TikTok wasnt even a thing. +PGA Tour\r\n\r\nZoom out, and this is a redemption arc dripping in irony. For years, McIlroy was the guy destined to dominate, until nerves, Nike deals, and swing coach roulette got in the way. Every April, the media would breathlessly ask Is this Rorys year? and then pretend not to look disappointed when he faceplanted on the back nine. But now? Rorys wearing the jacket, cashing a record-breaking $4.2 million cheque, and proving that if you stall long enough, the plot twist will eventually land. +TalkSport\r\n\r\nAs for the update: McIlroy is basking in green glory while Rose nurses his trauma with polite British resentment. Rorys caddie Harry Diamond pocketed $420k, which is great because someone needs to carry all that ego. Augustas curse is broken. Somewhere, Greg Norman is quietly seething. +NYPost', 0, 'factabot', 'Rory_McIlroy_Completes_Career_Grand_Slam_at_The_Masters', 'draft', NULL, NULL, '2025-04-15 07:25:07', '2025-04-15 07:43:29', 1);
INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (387, 'Dutton Clarifies Housing Plan: \'Don\'t Want Prices to Go Down\'', 'Opposition leader assures homeowners their property values are safe under his watch.', 'Peter Dutton, in a stunning display of saying the quiet part very loud, has clarified his big, bold housing policy: he doesnt want house prices to go down. Thats right. In a country where half the population is considering swapping avocado toast for sleeping in their cars, Dutton has confirmed hes not here to fix the housing crisisjust make it a bit more comfortable for people already in the club. +ABC\r\n\r\nHis plan? A thrilling new tax break for first-home buyers, letting them deduct mortgage interest for five years. Sounds nice, until you realise its like handing out free petrol during a traffic jamit doesnt fix the problem, it just makes everyone slam on the accelerator. Economists, aka the party poopers of election season, have already flagged this as a fast-track to making prices even higher. Because when you throw cash at demand without building more supply, what could possibly go wrong? +News.com.au\r\n\r\nDutton insists hes just trying to protect the value of peoples homes. Translation: Sorry renters, were keeping the property ladder just out of reach because falling prices might make Karen from Camberwell feel poor. He even dodged questions about whether hed help his own kids buy a housepossibly because the answer is yes, with my MP salary and probably a casual apartment in Canberra. +The Guardian\r\n\r\nAs for the latest twist, Duttons standing by his not-actually-a-solution solution, despite everyone from housing experts to your cousin with a TikTok account pointing out that its wildly counterproductive. Meanwhile, Labors building promises and the Greens are dreaming of unicorn housing policiesbut Dutton? Hes just here to make sure no boomers equity ever sheds a dollar. +SBS', 0, 'factabot', 'Dutton_Clarifies_Housing_Plan_Dont_Want_Prices_to_Go_Down', 'draft', '', NULL, '2025-04-15 07:28:08', '2025-04-15 07:34:13', 0);
