INSERT INTO `news_old_new` VALUES (14, 1, 'Australia\'s Two-Tier Economy: Prawns for the Rich, Instant Noodles for the Rest', 'A woman spends $60 on a prawn entre and declares Australia has a \"two-tier economy.\" Meanwhile, the rest of us are just trying to afford avocado toast.', 'Australias Two-Tier Economy: Prawns for the Rich, Instant Noodles for the Rest\r\nThe Players: The $60 Prawn Lady vs. The Struggling Masses\r\nMeet Australias latest economic philosopher: a woman who ordered a prawn entre, paid $60 for it, and had a revelationAustralia has a two-tier economy. Yes, folks, never mind the rising cost of living, the housing crisis, or stagnant wages; the moment of truth arrived between bites of overpriced seafood. While she dined in a bustling restaurant full of people apparently rolling in disposable income, she had an epiphany: some people can still afford luxury, while others are rationing their instant ramen. Groundbreaking. Someone alert the Reserve Bank.\r\nThe Drama: Bougie Dining vs. Budget Survival\r\nThis whole two-tier economy debate isnt new. For years, experts (you know, actual economists) have been pointing out that Australia is splitting into the haves and have-nots at an alarming rate. But somehow, nothing hits quite like seeing a full restaurant while you\'re crying into your Coles-branded spaghetti. With house prices at nosebleed levels and inflation turning basic groceries into luxury goods, its not shocking that some Aussies are wondering why certain people are still out here popping bottles while others are calculating whether they can afford an extra egg this week.\r\nThe Big Picture: Whos Actually Feeling the Squeeze?\r\nThe real kicker? The people who feel the crisis most arent the ones making headlines about it. Renters, minimum-wage workers, and single-income families arent splurging on fancy entreestheyre juggling bills and praying their landlords dont renovate them out of their homes. Meanwhile, cashed-up professionals, property investors, and anyone who bought real estate before 2015 seem to be doing just fine, thank you very much. The economy isnt collapsing for everyoneits just squeezing the life out of anyone who isnt already ahead. But sure, lets focus on restaurant crowds instead of, say, wage stagnation or corporate price gouging.\r\nThe Latest: Another Day, Another Shocking Observation\r\nThe internet has, of course, gone wild with reactionssome people nodding along, others rolling their eyes at the obviousness of it all. Meanwhile, economists continue to publish actual reports showing how wealth inequality is growing, but who has time for data when we have dramatic prawn-related anecdotes? The government, as usual, will probably announce a review of cost-of-living pressures before promptly doing absolutely nothing. Bon apptit, Australia!', 0, 'Paijo', 'Australia\'s_TwoTier_Economy:_Prawns_for_the_Rich,_Instant_Noodles_for_the_Rest', 'published', 'images/news/2LMl0JjNn68rC3JIz8QSBTdMvUtrUa8hBTmsVlFK.webp', '2025-03-03 09:55:42', '2025-03-12 07:19:04', 0);
